article.headline: San Francisco 73, Cal Poly-SLO 62
article.story: SAN FRANCISCO (AP)Dior Lowhorn picked up where he left off last season, scoring a game-high 22 points to help San Francisco beat Cal Poly 73-62 Friday in the season opener for both teams. Lowhorn, the West Coast Conference's top scorer in 2008-09 at 20.1 points per game, had 16 in the first half as the Dons (1-0) opened a 44-28 lead. Jordan Lewis led with 12 points for Cal Poly (0-1), which trailed by double digits for much of new coach Joe Callero's first game with the Mustangs.
